To get DBUS operational you need to start system bus service at system 
startup:

# dbus-daemon-1 --system

And then for every user session:

$ dbus-daemon-1 --session

process running in you system to work it propertly.

you can run it with while you login with script like this:

if test -z "$DBUS_SESSION_BUS_ADDRESS" ; then
  ## if not found, launch a new one 
  eval `dbus-launch --sh-syntax --exit-with-session`
  echo "D-BUS per-session daemon address is: $DBUS_SESSION_BUS_ADDRESS"
fi


#####

Protocols handlers:

Tlen.pl		tlen://
Gadu-Gadu	gg://
Jabber		jabber://
AIM		aim://
ICQ		icq://
EMAIL		email://


##### interface org.freedesktop.im #####

[org.freedesktop.im.getProtocols()]
    RETURN: 
	DBUS_TYPE_STRING's with supported protocols list example: gg:// jabber:// icq://


[org.freedesktop.im.getPresence( contactURI )]
    example: jabber://krzak@jabberpl.org
    
    RETURN: (DBUS_TYPE_UINT32 DBusIMPresence,
	     DBUS_TYPE_STRING status_description,
	     DBUS_TYPE_STRING icon_path)
    
	typedef enum
	{
	    IM_PRESENCE_NOT_FOUND = 1
	    IM_PRESENCE_AVAILABLE,
	    IM_PRESENCE_AWAY,
	    IM_PRESENCE_OFFLINE
	} DBusIMPresence;
	
	status_description - may be empty string "" [not NULL]
	icon_path - path to icon of this presence (optional, may be empty string "" [not NULL])

[org.freedesktop.im.openChat( contactURI )]
    RETURN: (DBUS_TYPE_BOOLEAN result)
